             in Petticoat-lane; that she offered to sell him seven shirts and a pair of sheets, and said he should have them reasonably; that three of them were new and four old; and that he believed the shirts produced to be the same, from the shortness of them; that as he did not like them he did not ask her how she came by them.</p>
